01:43.725 --> 01:44.724
Hey.

01:44.726 --> 01:47.293
Hi.

01:49.197 --> 01:51.664
I know we have a lot to talk about,

01:51.666 --> 01:53.466
but I don't, I don't want to get into

01:53.468 --> 01:55.067
any of that right now.

01:55.069 --> 01:56.869
I don't want to talk about us or Enzo

01:56.871 --> 01:58.652
or Stefan or anything,

01:58.655 --> 02:00.740
except the trouble headed our way.

02:03.991 --> 02:06.238
You are gonna need this.

02:09.050 --> 02:11.384
So the victim was here until you closed.

02:11.386 --> 02:12.685
Did he say where he was going?

02:12.687 --> 02:14.353
If he was meeting up with anyone?

02:14.355 --> 02:15.688
No.

02:17.892 --> 02:19.863
- Give me a minute.
- Okay.

02:21.596 --> 02:23.963
- Dad, when did you get back?
- Just this morning.

02:23.965 --> 02:25.865
Hey, look, I would've called ahead,

02:25.867 --> 02:27.923
but I wanted to tell you in person.

02:27.926 --> 02:29.826
[door creaks open]

02:31.673 --> 02:33.306
Mom?

02:33.308 --> 02:34.907
Hi, Matty.

02:34.909 --> 02:36.709
Hey, I, uh, thought you were gonna

02:36.711 --> 02:38.338
give me a minute with him first.

02:38.341 --> 02:39.378
I saw you two talking.

02:39.380 --> 02:40.746
I couldn't wait to see my son.

02:40.748 --> 02:43.720
After waiting four years
since your last phone message?

02:43.723 --> 02:46.018
As I remember, I asked
you to call me back.

02:46.020 --> 02:48.087
Hey, look, look, I know it's sudden,

02:48.089 --> 02:50.189
but you gave me a second chance.

02:50.191 --> 02:51.757
Didn't turn out so bad, right?

02:51.759 --> 02:53.359
I thought you hated him for leaving us.

02:53.361 --> 02:55.661
That was a lifetime ago.

02:55.663 --> 02:57.129
Things have changed since then.

02:57.131 --> 02:59.765
I was... I was actually
glad to hear from him.

02:59.768 --> 03:01.683
I was hoping we could
all get dinner tonight.

03:01.686 --> 03:03.366
[phone chimes]

03:06.205 --> 03:08.614
I'm not sure I'll be free.

03:11.443 --> 03:13.443
All right, professor,

03:13.445 --> 03:15.378
how do we get rid of the queen of hell?

03:15.380 --> 03:17.271
Are you sure Katherine's in our world?

03:17.274 --> 03:19.850
When Cade crossed planes after
the 11th ring of the bell,

03:19.852 --> 03:21.451
other souls could step through, too.

03:21.453 --> 03:22.586
Same way Kai did.

03:22.588 --> 03:24.888
Katherine would have
jumped at that chance.

03:24.890 --> 03:26.990
Then why haven't we seen her yet?

03:26.992 --> 03:28.191
I thought by now she'd be

03:28.193 --> 03:30.060
strutting around, making demands,

03:30.062 --> 03:31.995
or trying to get us all killed.

03:31.997 --> 03:33.864
Maybe she's biding her time.

03:33.866 --> 03:35.757
Or putting her own plan together.

03:35.760 --> 03:37.501
Either way, you're
gonna need a new weapon.

03:37.503 --> 03:39.369
Is that Dorian?

03:39.371 --> 03:42.105
Yeah, I've asked Dorian to take point

03:42.107 --> 03:43.373
on our research front.

03:43.375 --> 03:45.575
This doesn't mean you and I are cool.

03:45.577 --> 03:47.811
I still have those files on you, so

03:47.813 --> 03:49.446
I'm here to hold you accountable

03:49.448 --> 03:50.914
for the rest of your God-given life.

03:50.916 --> 03:54.570
I hope that you do.

03:54.573 --> 03:56.419
So what have you guys come up with?

03:56.421 --> 03:59.422
Cade was killed with a dagger
that was made from his bones.

03:59.424 --> 04:01.658
It was fused into glass
by a white-hot flame.

04:01.660 --> 04:03.460
First things first, though,

04:03.462 --> 04:06.463
I don't suppose you know
where Katherine's bones are?

04:06.465 --> 04:08.754
Oh, who'd have ever thought
she'd have done us a favor?

04:08.757 --> 04:10.767
We've got every last
one of Katherine's bones

04:10.769 --> 04:11.894
in the cave,

04:11.897 --> 04:13.436
underneath the old church,

04:13.438 --> 04:15.105
left over from a traveler barbecue

04:15.107 --> 04:18.007
she had when she tried to possess Elena.

04:18.010 --> 04:20.577
But fusing the bones into glass...

04:20.579 --> 04:22.112
How do we make that kind of weapon?

04:22.113 --> 04:24.881
Would putting the bone in
a metal dagger do the trick?

04:24.883 --> 04:27.304
My parents are in town. I
could ask my dad for help.

04:27.307 --> 04:29.186
"Parents," plural?

04:29.188 --> 04:30.687
Unexpected family reunion,

04:30.689 --> 04:32.989
so now I've got two
nightmares to deal with.

04:32.991 --> 04:34.591
Gossip later, townies.

04:34.593 --> 04:37.222
Stefan and I will go
on bone-fetching duty.

04:37.225 --> 04:40.563
Dorian and I will research
an alternative to fight her.

04:40.566 --> 04:42.532
See, if Katherine's back,

04:42.534 --> 04:44.100
that means hell still exists.

04:44.102 --> 04:46.303
We need to figure out a way
to break her link to hell.

04:46.305 --> 04:49.206
BONNIE: These psychic dimensions
are tied to emotional trauma.

04:49.208 --> 04:51.708
Cade created his when he
was burned at the stake.

04:51.710 --> 04:56.246
I created mine... when
I saw Enzo get murdered.

04:56.958 --> 04:59.025
I'm just saying maybe there's a way

04:59.028 --> 05:00.650
to destroy the dimension itself.

05:00.652 --> 05:02.085
Destroying hell destroys her.

05:02.087 --> 05:05.488
Great. You guys are on
Hail Mary miracle duty,

05:05.490 --> 05:08.358
so how do the rest of us get
Katherine to show herself?

05:08.360 --> 05:09.860
Easy.

05:09.862 --> 05:11.328
She's obsessed with Stefan

05:11.330 --> 05:13.096
and insanely jealous.

05:13.098 --> 05:15.799
If she sees anyone making him happy,

05:15.801 --> 05:17.734
she won't be able to control herself.

05:17.736 --> 05:20.337
So she'll have no choice
but to come out of hiding.

05:20.339 --> 05:22.439
- Your point?
- My point is

05:22.441 --> 05:24.808
we shove Stefan's happiness in her face.

05:24.810 --> 05:28.044
We throw the one party
Katherine would never miss.

05:30.496 --> 05:32.496
Who doesn't love a wedding?

05:36.161 --> 05:38.169
Sure, Caroline, get married.

05:38.172 --> 05:40.290
The day you've dreamt
of your whole life,

05:40.292 --> 05:41.725
just throw it together like some

05:41.727 --> 05:43.360
shotgun Vegas wedding

05:43.362 --> 05:44.828
to lure out and murder your nemesis,

05:44.830 --> 05:46.496
all before the vows are over.

05:46.498 --> 05:49.032
Yeah, it's happening fast.

05:58.545 --> 06:01.686
I never got to explain to
you why I said yes to Stefan.

06:01.689 --> 06:04.547
I know why you said yes.

06:04.549 --> 06:07.186
You want to spend your life with him,

06:07.189 --> 06:08.755
in spite of everything.

06:10.589 --> 06:13.346
I get it, but

06:13.349 --> 06:15.182
I can't watch you marry him.

06:15.185 --> 06:18.720
Can't watch him be happy.

06:18.723 --> 06:21.031
And it's really hard for me to say

06:21.033 --> 06:23.466
that I won't be there with you.

06:23.468 --> 06:26.603
Because you know I would
do anything for you.

06:26.605 --> 06:29.506
I can't do that to myself.

06:29.508 --> 06:31.141
I won't.

06:35.314 --> 06:37.106
I understand.

06:40.419 --> 06:41.882
I'm so sorry.

06:43.255 --> 06:44.858
I'm sorry in ways

06:44.861 --> 06:47.316
that I didn't even know existed.

06:50.128 --> 06:52.729
I know that I am one step removed

06:52.731 --> 06:55.298
from the reason that you lost Enzo.

06:55.300 --> 06:59.469
So I am extremely grateful
that you're even sitting here

06:59.471 --> 07:01.170
being my friend right now.

07:03.241 --> 07:06.710
Bonnie, I love you so much.

07:06.712 --> 07:09.179
So much.

07:09.181 --> 07:10.443
Please know that.

07:10.446 --> 07:11.539
I do.

07:11.542 --> 07:13.742
I know you do.

07:21.893 --> 07:23.626
DAMON: How are those vows coming?

07:23.628 --> 07:27.397
I'm gonna go out on a limb and say that

07:27.399 --> 07:30.137
Katherine won't let the
ceremony get that far.

07:30.140 --> 07:32.435
Caroline and Bonnie are
probably already rehearsing.

07:32.437 --> 07:34.098
You don't want to seem unprepared.

07:39.111 --> 07:43.847
Look... what happened to Enzo

07:43.849 --> 07:45.815
is gonna haunt you

07:45.817 --> 07:47.450
and her for the rest of your lives.

07:47.452 --> 07:51.089
But the you standing with me right now,

07:51.092 --> 07:53.656
the you that's gonna marry
Caroline Forbes tomorrow,

07:53.658 --> 07:57.494
the you that I have known
for almost 200 years...

07:57.496 --> 07:59.062
You didn't do it.

08:00.198 --> 08:05.368
Evil, nasty, Ripper Stefan did it.

08:05.370 --> 08:07.103
And you are not him.

08:07.105 --> 08:09.806
You hear me?

08:09.808 --> 08:11.207
Yeah.

08:11.209 --> 08:13.343
Good.

08:15.013 --> 08:18.581
Did you know you can
get ordained online?

08:18.583 --> 08:20.283
DAMON: Did it this morning.

08:20.285 --> 08:24.487
You are looking at a bona
fide justice of the peace.

08:24.489 --> 08:26.356
[Damon groans]

08:26.358 --> 08:28.591
Rise and shine, kitty cat.

08:32.264 --> 08:34.496
Hi, I'm Katherine,

08:34.499 --> 08:36.698
the bitch that will destroy your lives

08:36.701 --> 08:39.736
for all eternity! [laughs]

08:39.738 --> 08:42.438
Uh, okay, why don't we
just, uh, get what we need

08:42.441 --> 08:43.673
and get out of here.

08:43.674 --> 08:45.475
It's pretty fitting, though.

08:45.477 --> 08:47.277
The woman that started this whole mess

08:47.279 --> 08:48.511
is back to try and end it.

08:48.513 --> 08:50.713
I wouldn't say it was all a mess.

08:50.715 --> 08:52.015
What are you talking about?

08:52.017 --> 08:54.184
Look at the path that she sent us down.

08:54.186 --> 08:57.699
Ripper sprees, the
Originals, the cure, Silas,

08:57.702 --> 08:59.527
- the Other Side...
- I'm just saying that...

08:59.530 --> 09:02.458
Prison worlds, Gemini twins, Heretics,

09:02.461 --> 09:04.260
and don't get me started on

09:04.262 --> 09:06.910
doppelgangers! [laughs]

09:06.913 --> 09:09.532
I'm just saying we had some good things

09:09.534 --> 09:11.468
happen to us, too, right?

09:11.470 --> 09:14.037
That's very glass-half-full
of you, brother.

09:14.039 --> 09:16.339
Well, I have to think
that way, otherwise I go

09:16.341 --> 09:18.652
- to a very dark place.
- All right, all right,

09:18.655 --> 09:21.222
before this turns into a sob-fest.

09:24.349 --> 09:26.427
Happy bachelor party, little brother.

09:29.646 --> 09:31.955
Oh, you can celebrate with us, too.

09:31.957 --> 09:34.157
[making chugging sounds]

09:34.964 --> 09:37.093
Sorry for the lack of
exotic dancers... you know,

09:37.095 --> 09:40.130
short notice and all.

09:40.132 --> 09:44.167
Oh, this place hasn't changed a bit.

09:44.169 --> 09:45.802
There's my table.

09:45.804 --> 09:48.171
Vicki used to fill my glass on the sly.

09:50.809 --> 09:52.108
Why are you really here?

09:55.280 --> 09:58.748
I've had a lot of time to
think these last few years.

09:58.750 --> 10:00.950
I stopped dwelling on the past.

10:00.952 --> 10:03.953
I want to do things better now.

10:03.955 --> 10:06.723
People do change, believe it or not.

10:09.995 --> 10:13.596
I know this is a lot for you, Matty.

10:13.598 --> 10:15.665
But I miss my family.

10:19.905 --> 10:22.372
[sniffles, chuckles]

10:23.945 --> 10:25.775
Don't worry, I won't get all weepy

10:25.777 --> 10:27.293
before the drinks arrive.

10:51.503 --> 10:53.970
TRUDY: She told me not to
post video, but screw her.

10:53.972 --> 10:57.840
Everyone should know what a slut she is.

10:57.842 --> 10:59.403
Uh, what is that?

11:00.395 --> 11:03.813
It's disgusting, isn't it?

11:03.815 --> 11:07.750
It's what happens when
you get older... and die,

11:07.752 --> 11:10.086
come back from hell.

11:10.088 --> 11:12.255
It's really rough on the body.

11:13.768 --> 11:16.593
But there is a short-term remedy.

11:16.595 --> 11:18.294
[screams]

11:38.568 --> 11:39.804
_

11:39.807 --> 11:42.631
_

11:43.897 --> 11:45.889
DAMON: All right, bulletin.

11:47.148 --> 11:49.215
Human Stefan is a lightweight.

11:49.218 --> 11:50.467
Damon.

11:50.470 --> 11:52.653
- Oh, God.
- This is not my fault, Caroline.

11:52.655 --> 11:53.821
Impromptu weddings

11:53.823 --> 11:55.956
call for impromptu bachelor parties.

11:55.958 --> 11:58.892
[groans]

11:58.894 --> 12:01.161
Oh, please, don't be
mad at me, Caroline.

12:01.163 --> 12:04.198
I'm not mad at you.

12:04.200 --> 12:06.266
Thank you for my present, by the way.

12:07.069 --> 12:08.635
Looks like I am gonna need

12:08.637 --> 12:09.870
a new drinking buddy.

12:09.872 --> 12:11.071
Pass.

12:11.073 --> 12:12.606
Oh, come on.

12:12.608 --> 12:14.141
It's your last night as a single gal.

12:14.143 --> 12:16.076
Let's blow this popsicle stand.

12:16.078 --> 12:17.544
- [groans]
- No.

12:17.546 --> 12:19.980
That is a $10,000 rug.

12:19.982 --> 12:21.415
Psst.

12:23.886 --> 12:26.086
[Stefan groaning]

12:34.897 --> 12:37.397
♪ A love that's there ♪

12:37.399 --> 12:40.868
♪ For others, too ♪

12:40.870 --> 12:46.707
♪ I'm a fool to holdhoou... ♪

12:48.744 --> 12:52.779
Perhaps you should consider
a less melancholy playlist.

12:52.781 --> 12:56.149
Helps me stay connected to you.

12:56.151 --> 12:58.285
[exhales]

12:58.287 --> 13:01.722
You don't need pain to
keep our connection alive.

13:01.724 --> 13:03.156
You are a witch, after all.

13:03.158 --> 13:05.792
A witch who can't do magic.

13:05.794 --> 13:07.528
What do you call my presence, then?

13:16.338 --> 13:18.872
Clearly, I'm not a hallucination.

13:18.874 --> 13:21.642
There has to be magic involved;

13:21.644 --> 13:24.678
therefore, you don't need pain.

13:24.680 --> 13:26.213
Therefore, you can attend the wedding

13:26.215 --> 13:28.015
without fear of losing your link to me.

13:28.017 --> 13:30.918
That's not why I'm skipping the wedding.

13:30.920 --> 13:32.653
Stefan murdered you.

13:32.655 --> 13:35.322
That version of Stefan

13:35.324 --> 13:37.891
died when you gave him the cure.

13:37.893 --> 13:40.494
The real Stefan is back.

13:40.496 --> 13:42.400
He's the one who's
getting married tomorrow.

13:42.403 --> 13:45.966
Maybe when I'm dead I'll
be as evolved as you,

13:45.968 --> 13:49.570
but that is not how I feel about him.

13:52.103 --> 13:53.740
Then trust Caroline.

13:55.711 --> 13:59.413
Trust how she feels.

13:59.415 --> 14:01.148
Share in her happiness.

14:01.150 --> 14:02.849
It won't negate ours.

14:07.423 --> 14:09.723
Are you actually happy?

14:09.725 --> 14:12.693
Certainly, luv.

14:16.231 --> 14:19.433
I'm imagining us next to
a little church I remember

14:19.435 --> 14:21.668
in the French countryside.

14:21.670 --> 14:23.971
It's in the middle of a lavender field.

14:23.973 --> 14:27.207
I always thought it would be
the perfect place to marry you.

14:29.676 --> 14:33.473
And after our wedding, we'd dance.

14:36.456 --> 14:40.354
And I'd tell you how much I love you.

14:40.356 --> 14:43.056
And I'd tell you the absolute truth,

14:43.059 --> 14:46.761
which is I'm the luckiest
man on the face of the Earth.

14:59.274 --> 15:01.808
All right. I got one more.

15:01.810 --> 15:05.212
No. No more practice speeches.

15:05.214 --> 15:07.147
- Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.
- [groans]

15:07.149 --> 15:08.482
Okay, listen.

15:08.484 --> 15:09.750
Come on, come on.

15:09.752 --> 15:12.219
Up.

15:12.221 --> 15:14.321
To a Mystic Falls mom

15:14.323 --> 15:17.391
who started out by hating me,

15:17.393 --> 15:20.427
and became one of my closest friends.

15:20.429 --> 15:24.164
She was strong. She was loving.

15:24.166 --> 15:26.266
And not only did she protect this town,

15:26.268 --> 15:28.335
but she raised an incredible daughter...

15:28.337 --> 15:30.437
[lightly chuckles]

15:30.439 --> 15:33.840
...that I now get to call family.

15:35.269 --> 15:37.678
To Liz Forbes.

15:38.914 --> 15:43.150
Gone... but never forgotten.

15:48.418 --> 15:49.990
God, I miss her.

15:49.992 --> 15:50.957
I know.

15:50.959 --> 15:55.128
I hate that she is not here.

15:55.130 --> 15:56.963
[laughs dryly]

15:56.965 --> 16:00.757
And Bonnie's not coming,
my girls can't be there,

16:00.760 --> 16:02.102
Elena won't be there.

16:02.104 --> 16:03.336
Hold that thought.

16:03.338 --> 16:08.108
So, I remember when you gave me this...

16:08.110 --> 16:09.476
at Christmas.

16:09.478 --> 16:10.811
You said it was for future me.

16:10.813 --> 16:13.480
A guy who'd one day ask
for your forgiveness.

16:13.482 --> 16:15.164
Is this you asking?

16:15.167 --> 16:18.551
Let's save that for another
Salvatore bonding night,

16:18.554 --> 16:20.554
- why don't we?
- [chuckles]

16:22.887 --> 16:24.491
I just wanted you to know that Elena

16:24.493 --> 16:26.660
would be with you tomorrow.

16:31.300 --> 16:34.301
But just so we're clear...

16:34.303 --> 16:36.036
I want that back.

16:36.038 --> 16:38.338
[laughs]

16:38.340 --> 16:40.974
Something borrowed.

16:40.976 --> 16:42.576
Got it.

16:46.248 --> 16:47.851
[sighs]

17:32.623 --> 17:34.557
[sighs]

17:45.194 --> 17:47.027
- There she is!
- Mommy!

17:47.029 --> 17:49.930
Oh! Ooh!

17:49.933 --> 17:53.433
Oh, you girls look amazing.

17:53.436 --> 17:54.702
Ooh.

17:54.704 --> 17:58.072
But I thought we decided it wasn't safe.

17:58.074 --> 17:59.406
ALARIC: Yeah, well, you and I

17:59.408 --> 18:00.908
both know that Katherine
would smell a rat

18:00.910 --> 18:02.176
if they weren't there.

18:02.178 --> 18:06.414
So... Stefan called in
a favor from Valerie.

18:06.417 --> 18:08.549
It turns out she has a
soft spot for Gemini twins.

18:08.551 --> 18:10.985
She put a protection spell on them,

18:10.987 --> 18:12.887
so they'll be safe no matter what.

18:12.889 --> 18:15.322
Thank you for bringing them.

18:15.324 --> 18:17.112
Daddy, come practice with us.

18:17.115 --> 18:18.292
Oh, I'd love to, sweetheart,

18:18.294 --> 18:19.875
but Daddy has to go back to work.

18:21.163 --> 18:22.930
You understand, right?

18:22.932 --> 18:25.266
Of course.

18:26.269 --> 18:28.435
[giggles]

18:29.872 --> 18:32.673
- Ric...
- JOSIE: Can I wear this?

18:33.643 --> 18:35.476
Uh, I'm pretty sure that's Mommy's.

18:36.546 --> 18:40.381
That is my something new.

18:40.383 --> 18:41.949
Do you want to help me put it on?

18:41.951 --> 18:43.584
- Uh-huh.
[giggles] - Yeah.

18:43.586 --> 18:46.954
[whispering]: Ah, thank you.

18:46.956 --> 18:48.556
[Caroline and Josie giggle]

18:48.558 --> 18:50.573
I also have something blue,

18:50.576 --> 18:53.394
something old, and something borrowed.

18:53.396 --> 18:55.296
[whispering]: Mommy looks so pretty.

18:55.298 --> 18:57.998
- [Josie giggles]
- Yes, yes, she does.

19:05.508 --> 19:06.807
[sighs]

19:09.812 --> 19:12.379
Be happy, Caroline.

19:23.526 --> 19:26.493
Uh... yeah.

19:26.495 --> 19:28.662
[girls giggling]

19:39.775 --> 19:42.142
Peter.

19:44.080 --> 19:46.013
Didn't expect you to be so cleaned up.

19:46.015 --> 19:48.182
[laughs] Well, it is a wedding.

19:48.184 --> 19:49.116
I thought you'd come straight

19:49.118 --> 19:51.151
from your workshop with the dagger.

19:51.153 --> 19:54.321
The one they asked you to
make from Katherine's bones.

19:56.959 --> 19:59.093
I'm surprised Matt told you about it.

19:59.095 --> 20:00.694
I didn't think he'd want
to involve you in all this.

20:00.696 --> 20:02.296
Well, if we're gonna be a family again,

20:02.298 --> 20:04.365
we need to be honest with each other.

20:07.036 --> 20:08.435
Okay, then yes.

20:08.437 --> 20:10.471
Yeah, I... I finished
in time to take a shower

20:10.473 --> 20:11.939
so I could get here a little early.

20:11.941 --> 20:14.274
And where's the dagger?

20:16.178 --> 20:18.212
[sighs]

20:18.214 --> 20:20.014
I gave it to Stefan already.

20:22.184 --> 20:24.051
[vomits]

20:24.053 --> 20:26.887
Hey, are you okay?

20:26.889 --> 20:28.722
Honestly, no.

20:36.032 --> 20:37.631
Maybe I should hold onto that.

20:37.633 --> 20:41.101
No, I'm the bait. I should.

20:41.103 --> 20:44.438
Hey.

20:44.440 --> 20:47.741
Know this.

20:47.743 --> 20:49.843
If she lays a hand on you,

20:49.845 --> 20:52.212
I will cut her up into
tiny, little pieces

20:52.214 --> 20:56.617
and I will serve her
at the wedding buffet.

20:59.121 --> 21:04.758
Hope I get to see you have
this one day with Elena.

21:04.760 --> 21:07.428
A wedding, a human life...

21:07.430 --> 21:09.730
all of it.

21:09.732 --> 21:13.300
I want you to be there, too, brother.

21:13.302 --> 21:15.302
'Cause I'm gonna need a best man.

21:15.304 --> 21:16.937
[chuckles softly]

21:16.939 --> 21:20.808
Hopefully your hero hair
hasn't fallen out by then.

21:25.381 --> 21:27.181
[exhales]

21:28.651 --> 21:30.451
[string quartet begins playing]

21:33.255 --> 21:35.255
Where's Dad?

21:35.257 --> 21:37.191
I haven't seen him all day.

21:37.193 --> 21:39.059
I'm sure he'll be here soon.

21:39.061 --> 21:41.628
STEFAN: By the way, I
think you may have gone

21:41.630 --> 21:45.599
a little bit overboard with
the number of compelled guests.

21:45.601 --> 21:48.068
DAMON: Well, I mean, Stefan,

21:48.070 --> 21:49.503
it had to look authentic.

21:49.505 --> 21:51.819
Katherine knows your
girl's not gonna have

21:51.822 --> 21:53.689
a small, intimate gathering.

21:53.692 --> 21:55.258
Ah.

21:59.510 --> 22:02.544
Traditional opening waltz
of the Founder's Ball.

22:02.546 --> 22:06.915
The exact same one you and
Katherine danced to in 1864.

22:08.652 --> 22:12.321
She won't be able to resist.

22:12.323 --> 22:14.523
CAROLINE: You girls will
go in front of Mommy,

22:14.525 --> 22:17.993
and then Mommy will just
walk herself down the aisle,

22:17.995 --> 22:20.596
and it will all be fine.

22:22.967 --> 22:24.162
BONNIE: Or...

22:27.304 --> 22:29.137
...I could walk with you.

22:29.139 --> 22:31.840
Oh, my God.

22:31.842 --> 22:33.008
You're here.

22:33.010 --> 22:35.010
[crying]: Oh...

22:35.012 --> 22:36.878
I have a selfish reason.

22:38.549 --> 22:40.315
I want to be a part of your happiness.

22:40.317 --> 22:41.783
[laughs]

22:41.785 --> 22:44.019
Always.

22:44.786 --> 22:46.955
Mommy, are you ready?

22:47.958 --> 22:49.524
Now I'm ready.

22:49.526 --> 22:50.826
[giggles]

22:50.828 --> 22:52.696
My best friend's here.

23:05.582 --> 23:06.915
[phone chimes]

23:07.751 --> 23:09.735
_

23:10.114 --> 23:12.648
[inhales]

23:23.531 --> 23:26.110
[exhales] Check this out.
So I've been reading about

23:26.113 --> 23:29.288
psychic energy manipulation.
If we could create

23:29.290 --> 23:31.690
a massive amount of energy that breaches

23:31.692 --> 23:33.725
the psychic plane of hell,

23:33.727 --> 23:35.427
we might be able to destroy it.

23:35.429 --> 23:37.296
Kind of like how they
blow out oil well fires

23:37.298 --> 23:39.307
by creating an even bigger explosion.

23:39.310 --> 23:41.400
Except our explosion would be made

23:41.402 --> 23:44.469
of incredibly intense psychic energy.

23:47.274 --> 23:51.176
Or, we-we don't have to talk.

23:51.178 --> 23:55.047
What with your, your girl
getting married today and all,

23:55.049 --> 23:56.481
that's...

23:56.483 --> 23:58.483
You know what? You look
like you need bourbon.

23:58.485 --> 24:01.420
I should find some bourbon.

24:01.422 --> 24:03.589
Did I ever tell you why
I came to Mystic Falls?

24:05.192 --> 24:06.992
I was hunting Damon.

24:09.330 --> 24:11.864
He had killed my first wife.

24:11.866 --> 24:15.734
Then I found out he had turned her,

24:15.736 --> 24:20.105
and that was what she wanted.

24:23.510 --> 24:26.144
Eventually, I got past that.

24:26.146 --> 24:28.013
How?

24:28.015 --> 24:33.018
I guess I didn't have the
energy to hate somebody forever.

24:34.855 --> 24:39.825
<i>We've all made... terrible
mistakes in our lives.</i>

24:41.462 --> 24:44.396
<i>Done things that...</i>

24:44.398 --> 24:48.667
<i>no apology can heal.</i>

24:48.669 --> 24:54.057
<i>But you just have to keep going.</i>

24:55.843 --> 25:00.345
<i>Try to find some new happiness.</i>

25:01.894 --> 25:04.795
<i>No matter how much you've lost.</i>

25:07.588 --> 25:11.490
The strange thing is...

25:11.492 --> 25:16.328
losing those people is
what brought us together.

25:16.330 --> 25:18.497
It's how we found each other.

25:21.376 --> 25:24.670
It's what made us...

25:24.672 --> 25:26.247
a family.

25:29.410 --> 25:32.044
♪ ♪

25:54.868 --> 25:57.135
♪ ♪

26:24.365 --> 26:26.498
♪ ♪

26:38.479 --> 26:39.811
Where did you get that necklace?

26:39.813 --> 26:41.939
You gave it to me.

26:41.942 --> 26:43.268
No, I didn't. That's Katherine's.

26:43.271 --> 26:45.627
Seems she accepted our invitation.

26:45.630 --> 26:47.314
She snuck into our house?

26:47.317 --> 26:48.908
She's a villain. What do you expect?

26:48.911 --> 26:50.876
No, no, no. Keep it on.

26:50.879 --> 26:52.399
We want her to see you wearing it.

26:52.402 --> 26:53.818
You think she's already here?

26:53.820 --> 26:55.987
Dad should've been here by now.

26:55.989 --> 26:58.373
DAMON: Dearly beloved.

26:58.375 --> 27:00.825
We are gathered here today

27:00.827 --> 27:03.878
to witness the joining of
these two epic lovebirds

27:03.880 --> 27:06.381
in official matrimony.

27:06.383 --> 27:09.584
Stefan has found the
woman of his dreams,

27:09.586 --> 27:13.638
and he's going to share the
rest of his human life with her.

27:13.640 --> 27:16.257
But before we begin,

27:16.259 --> 27:18.930
if anyone has any
objections to this union,

27:18.933 --> 27:21.984
please speak now or
forever hold your peace.

27:22.816 --> 27:24.265
Yep.

27:24.267 --> 27:26.017
Speak right now.

27:26.019 --> 27:27.352
Anyone?

27:29.606 --> 27:33.074
As in... now.

27:33.076 --> 27:35.193
Right now.

27:36.413 --> 27:37.829
Well.

27:38.832 --> 27:41.366
Well, it seems like no one's objecting,

27:41.368 --> 27:43.868
so we will continue with the ceremony.

27:43.870 --> 27:44.953
We will?

27:44.955 --> 27:46.037
You betcha.

27:47.761 --> 27:49.340
Do you, Stefan,

27:49.342 --> 27:51.176
take this lovely woman

27:51.178 --> 27:53.178
to be your lawfully wedded wife?

27:55.632 --> 27:56.798
I do.

27:56.800 --> 27:59.184
And do you, Caroline,

27:59.186 --> 28:02.437
take this man to be your
lawfully wedded husband,

28:02.439 --> 28:06.558
to have and to hold, in
sickness and in health,

28:06.560 --> 28:08.893
till death do you part?

28:08.895 --> 28:10.728
I do.

28:10.730 --> 28:13.064
I believe the bride
and groom have chosen

28:13.066 --> 28:14.649
to write their own vows.

28:15.485 --> 28:17.035
We haven't.

28:17.459 --> 28:20.989
Oh. Well... just wing it.

28:20.991 --> 28:22.574
Go.

28:24.711 --> 28:27.128
Caroline.

28:27.130 --> 28:31.332
You have been my... my friend,

28:31.334 --> 28:32.967
my conscience,

28:32.969 --> 28:34.586
my sounding board.

28:34.588 --> 28:36.727
You saw light in me

28:36.730 --> 28:39.924
when all I saw was darkness.

28:39.926 --> 28:42.343
You saved me from despair.

28:43.930 --> 28:46.431
You told me once that I
would fall madly in love

28:46.433 --> 28:49.017
without realizing it.

28:49.019 --> 28:50.235
And that's what happened.

28:50.237 --> 28:52.186
[laughs softly]

28:52.188 --> 28:54.522
Day by day,

28:54.524 --> 28:58.943
bit by bit, year by year.

28:58.945 --> 29:00.778
With you.

29:00.780 --> 29:04.282
I remember saying that to you.

29:04.284 --> 29:07.869
We were dancing at my prom.

29:09.039 --> 29:11.039
It's funny the things we remember

29:11.041 --> 29:12.892
out of all the years that go by.

29:16.930 --> 29:19.964
I remember how you told me

29:19.966 --> 29:23.768
that when I was ready for
you, you would be ready for me.

29:25.305 --> 29:27.188
I'm ready now.

29:27.190 --> 29:29.307
I think a part of me

29:29.309 --> 29:31.476
has been ready for this
day since the moment

29:31.478 --> 29:33.227
I first saw you,

29:33.229 --> 29:37.565
the new mystery guy in
the hallway at school.

29:38.985 --> 29:40.868
[Caroline laughs softly]

29:40.870 --> 29:44.789
I will always remember this moment.

29:44.791 --> 29:47.875
A hundred years from now,

29:47.877 --> 29:52.330
I will remember this
moment for the both of us.

29:57.030 --> 29:59.304
Wow.

29:59.306 --> 30:00.722
Munchkins.

30:00.724 --> 30:01.839
Rings.

30:01.841 --> 30:03.808
Now.

30:12.519 --> 30:14.602
With this ring,

30:14.604 --> 30:16.237
I thee wed.

30:16.239 --> 30:18.272
[chuckles]

30:24.197 --> 30:26.497
With this ring,

30:26.499 --> 30:28.700
I thee wed.

30:31.121 --> 30:33.454
DAMON: With the power
recently vested in me

30:33.456 --> 30:37.208
by the Commonwealth of Virginia,

30:37.210 --> 30:40.261
I now pronounce you husband and wife.

30:40.263 --> 30:42.797
You may kiss the bride, little brother.

30:56.563 --> 30:58.863
♪ ♪

31:20.718 --> 31:25.560
- ♪ When our bodies fall apart ♪
- [Josie and Elizabeth laughing]

31:29.099 --> 31:33.435
♪ A broken puzzle of the past ♪

31:33.437 --> 31:37.856
Why send the necklace,
but skip the wedding?

31:37.858 --> 31:40.942
Maybe she wants to stand
you up for old times' sake.

31:40.944 --> 31:44.196
Hmm. So nice having you back, Bon.

31:44.198 --> 31:46.331
Warms my cold dead heart.

31:46.333 --> 31:50.619
♪ 'Cause honey, all
the good things left ♪

31:54.508 --> 31:57.342
♪ I will love you till the world ♪

31:57.344 --> 32:01.463
♪ Stops turning ♪

32:01.465 --> 32:06.435
♪ And ever after, when it comes ♪

32:09.473 --> 32:13.809
♪ And all the days between, I left ♪

32:13.811 --> 32:15.894
♪ For learning ♪

32:15.896 --> 32:19.114
♪ What this life's about ♪

32:23.404 --> 32:29.624
♪ So I'll love you till the
world stops turning round ♪

32:33.414 --> 32:37.666
♪ When your well is drying up ♪

32:41.171 --> 32:44.172
♪ Like a desert into dust ♪

32:44.174 --> 32:46.341
[gas hisses]

32:48.562 --> 32:52.347
♪ And there's no rain on the horizon ♪

32:56.437 --> 33:00.689
♪ I'll be there to fill your cup ♪

33:03.694 --> 33:08.280
♪ I will love you till
the world stops turning ♪

33:08.282 --> 33:10.599
Come on. Bathroom's this way, ladies.

33:10.601 --> 33:13.335
♪ And ever after... ♪

33:13.337 --> 33:15.504
Mom, where'd you go?

33:15.506 --> 33:17.756
You can't just bail in
the middle of a wedding.

33:17.758 --> 33:18.874
[phone beeps]

33:18.876 --> 33:21.593
[line ringing]

33:21.595 --> 33:25.180
[phone ringing nearby]

33:26.733 --> 33:28.600
[ringing continues]

33:28.719 --> 33:32.020
[ringing continues]

33:42.533 --> 33:43.899
[crickets chirping]

33:45.585 --> 33:47.953
Dad. Dad!

33:47.955 --> 33:51.990
Oh, you lost a lot of blood.

33:53.577 --> 33:55.377
We're lucky Katherine didn't kill you.

33:55.379 --> 33:57.212
Katherine didn't do this. I...

33:58.749 --> 34:02.717
DAMON: Paging the bride and groom.

34:02.719 --> 34:03.976
Thank you.

34:03.979 --> 34:06.968
It is now time for
everyone's favorite best man

34:06.971 --> 34:08.723
to make a little toast.

34:08.725 --> 34:10.475
[smacks lips, inhales slowly]

34:10.476 --> 34:12.060
Little brother,

34:12.062 --> 34:14.513
I have waited a hundred and...

34:15.167 --> 34:17.773
well, a whole lot of years,

34:17.775 --> 34:19.803
to make this speech.

34:19.804 --> 34:23.556
And today, I finally get
to tell my little brother...

34:23.559 --> 34:26.426
I'll take it from here,
gorgeous. [chuckles]

34:26.428 --> 34:27.761
He and I made out once.

34:27.763 --> 34:29.846
[in raspy voice]: Super hot.

34:29.848 --> 34:31.815
Drunken toast from Kelly Donovan.

34:31.818 --> 34:33.625
Perfect. Now it's a wedding.

34:33.628 --> 34:36.186
Well, I've known Stefan
Salvatore for years,

34:36.188 --> 34:37.771
but I can honestly say

34:37.773 --> 34:40.908
I'm not sure what all the fuss
is about. [chuckles]

34:40.911 --> 34:42.254
And then,

34:42.257 --> 34:45.411
there's little Mrs. Perfect. Aw.

34:45.414 --> 34:47.197
- Too mad your mother's dead.
- [guests gasp]

34:47.199 --> 34:48.916
Maybe if you hadn't
tried to cure cancer,

34:48.918 --> 34:50.918
she might have lived to see this.

34:50.920 --> 34:52.168
Okay, okay. Yeah, yeah.

34:52.170 --> 34:53.337
That's enough. Hey.

34:53.339 --> 34:54.838
Now go find the open bar.

34:54.840 --> 34:56.005
No.

34:56.007 --> 34:57.674
Damon.

34:58.794 --> 35:00.377
You're worse than either of them.

35:00.379 --> 35:02.462
What you did to Vicki? Shame on you.

35:03.599 --> 35:05.465
She didn't hurt anyone
ever. She might have

35:05.467 --> 35:08.018
turned her life around, but
you didn't give her the chance.

35:08.020 --> 35:09.937
Then again,

35:09.939 --> 35:11.772
I never had a chance, either.

35:11.774 --> 35:13.390
No, this town made up its mind

35:13.392 --> 35:16.059
about me... [scoffs] long time ago.

35:18.647 --> 35:21.514
You all looked right
through me for years.

35:21.517 --> 35:23.567
Treated me like a joke.

35:24.536 --> 35:28.038
Sent me packing without
a second thought.

35:28.040 --> 35:29.990
Maybe...

35:29.992 --> 35:32.209
if you hadn't forgotten all about me,

35:32.211 --> 35:33.910
you would have known

35:33.912 --> 35:36.388
that I had a bad fall two years ago.

35:36.391 --> 35:37.914
And...

35:37.916 --> 35:40.250
you never knew I was dead.

35:41.336 --> 35:45.055
No, the only one who gave a
damn about me was Katherine.

35:45.057 --> 35:46.423
She saw how I was

35:46.425 --> 35:47.724
suffering in hel...

35:48.510 --> 35:49.309
Where is she?

35:49.311 --> 35:50.560
[wretches]

35:50.562 --> 35:52.729
[guests gasp]

35:52.731 --> 35:55.649
I have no idea.

35:55.651 --> 35:58.685
I was busy causing a
gas leak in the house.

35:59.521 --> 36:01.605
Oh, my God. The girls.

36:01.607 --> 36:02.856
And Bonnie.

36:04.562 --> 36:07.444
You really think you could
play Katherine Pierce?

36:07.446 --> 36:08.912
[laughs]

36:39.734 --> 36:45.424
♪ ♪

36:48.929 --> 36:52.931
[Bonnie, Josie and Elizabeth coughing]

36:52.933 --> 36:55.184
It's okay.

36:55.186 --> 36:56.768
We're okay.

36:56.770 --> 36:58.904
Whatever you guys are
doing, keep doing it.

36:58.906 --> 37:00.572
Okay?

37:00.574 --> 37:02.908
ENZO: You have to keep moving, luv.

37:02.910 --> 37:05.110
You'll die if you stay here.

37:05.112 --> 37:07.412
I don't know how
they're even doing this.

37:07.414 --> 37:08.697
[girls coughing]

37:08.699 --> 37:10.212
Enzo?

37:10.215 --> 37:12.549
I think they're siphoning
directly from you.

37:14.224 --> 37:15.774
But I don't have any magic.

37:15.776 --> 37:17.868
Of course you do, luv.
How else do you think

37:17.871 --> 37:19.620
you've been able to
stay connected to me?

37:19.623 --> 37:20.967
[coughing continues]

37:20.970 --> 37:22.564
Let them siphon you, Bonnie.

37:22.566 --> 37:24.199
Tell them to use the magic to save you.

37:24.201 --> 37:25.867
- No.
- Look,

37:25.869 --> 37:27.486
I know that you think
we'll be parted forever

37:27.488 --> 37:29.538
if you let go of me now,
but I believe the opposite.

37:29.540 --> 37:30.572
Enzo.

37:30.574 --> 37:32.658
I believe the opposite.

37:34.238 --> 37:36.655
I believe we'll be together again.

37:38.053 --> 37:40.499
When I see you again,
there'll be only peace.

37:40.501 --> 37:42.551
And no one will ever part us.

37:43.837 --> 37:45.337
But right now,

37:45.339 --> 37:46.722
you need to fight!

37:46.724 --> 37:48.090
And you need to live.

37:49.009 --> 37:50.425
Please, Bonnie.

37:50.428 --> 37:52.061
Bonnie, you know in
your heart this is right.

37:52.062 --> 37:53.395
Do it now.

37:53.397 --> 37:54.680
Use your magic.

37:54.682 --> 37:57.099
Show them how to do the spell.

38:02.239 --> 38:05.524
Do what I do, okay?

38:06.694 --> 38:08.694
Say these words:

38:10.497 --> 38:13.782
Phesmatos motus incendiaros.

38:13.784 --> 38:15.917
Phesmatos...

38:15.919 --> 38:19.287
Live your life, Bonnie
Bennett. All of it.

38:19.290 --> 38:21.257
Promise me.

38:21.260 --> 38:23.375
[girls chanting]

38:23.377 --> 38:25.460
I promise.

38:25.462 --> 38:27.212
I love you.

38:27.214 --> 38:29.047
I love you...

38:35.522 --> 38:37.472
Phesmatos...

38:37.474 --> 38:40.275
motus incendiaros.

38:40.277 --> 38:41.193
Phesmatos...

38:41.195 --> 38:44.696
ALL: motus incendiaros.

38:44.698 --> 38:49.451
Phesmatos motus incendiaros.

38:49.453 --> 38:54.623
Phesmatos motus incendiaros.

38:54.625 --> 38:57.159
Phesmatos motus...

38:57.161 --> 38:59.161
incendiaros.

39:04.084 --> 39:05.667
[guests yell]

39:07.504 --> 39:10.338
[panicked murmuring]

39:11.508 --> 39:12.724
[coughs]

39:12.726 --> 39:14.676
- Mommy!
- Oh, my God.

39:15.679 --> 39:17.345
Oh...

39:17.347 --> 39:19.314
You're okay.

39:20.934 --> 39:23.852
Oh, my babies. [sighs]

39:25.498 --> 39:27.948
You're okay.

39:29.807 --> 39:31.359
What did Katherine promise you?

39:31.361 --> 39:32.277
Nothing.

39:32.279 --> 39:33.578
Then why help her?

39:33.580 --> 39:34.663
You don't get it.

39:34.665 --> 39:36.448
She promised me nothing...

39:36.450 --> 39:38.533
oblivion, emptiness.

39:38.535 --> 39:41.119
Anything is better than
endless torture in hell.

39:42.206 --> 39:45.423
And all I had to do was
keep you idiots distracted

39:45.425 --> 39:47.843
until the fire started.

39:47.845 --> 39:49.580
What is Katherine planning?

39:49.583 --> 39:52.547
You don't have to bully me.
She wanted me to let you know.

39:52.549 --> 39:55.717
She's gonna burn down Mystic Falls.

39:55.719 --> 39:57.385
With hellfire.

39:57.387 --> 39:58.854
Tonight.

39:58.856 --> 40:00.639
[chuckles]

40:00.641 --> 40:02.724
She's talking about the bell.

40:06.029 --> 40:09.064
Even if Katherine rings the
bell, she can't create hellfire.

40:09.066 --> 40:10.983
Only someone from the
Maxwell bloodline can do that.

40:10.985 --> 40:12.983
Dad's not gonna do it and neither am I.

40:12.986 --> 40:15.487
Oh, then it's a good thing
you weren't an only child.

40:18.625 --> 40:21.877
DAMON: Except Vicki's
dead as a doornail.

40:21.879 --> 40:23.245
KELLY: She was.

40:23.247 --> 40:25.213
Until my son opened up a portal

40:25.215 --> 40:28.133
to hell and let some people out.

40:28.135 --> 40:30.385
- [thunder cracks]
- [laughs]

40:34.893 --> 40:37.342
